<h2>Mining reforms:</h2>
<p>a. Indian iron-ore miners (15% royalty) are one of highest royalty payers in world.</p>
<p>b. Only 10% of geological potential is being mined.</p>
<p>c. Level playing field for private players and PSUs (eg: Goa mining issue)</p>
<p>d. low production by miners to manipulate demand pressure by restricting supply</p>
<p>e. EoDB due to problems like env clearances and fees/penalities acc to forest cons act</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Power reforms:</h2>
<p>a. Eliminate Cross Subsidization</p>
<p>b. Covering up AT&amp;C Losses: introduce 100% metering-net metering, smart meters.</p>
<p>c. Greening The Grid: The KUSUM scheme</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Oil n gas :</h2>
<p>GAS = 6 to 15% + 16,500 to 27000 km pipeline + 48% import&nbsp;<br />
OIL = 2nd largest oil&nbsp;refiner&nbsp; + 80% imported + 3rd largest energy consumer&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Challenges&nbsp;</h4>
<p>crude volatile + shale gas extraction not viable + fire in oil field like Baghjan assam&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Way forward&nbsp;</h4>
<p>CBM + IGX + Strategic reserve + Dynamic fuel pricing&nbsp;</p>
<p>move to Gas based economy + INDC achieve help</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>AVIATION</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>FDI upto 49% (NRI upto 100%)&nbsp; = FDI with protection from foreign influence&nbsp;</p>
<h3>India is set to be the 3rd largest aviation market in the world by 2024</h3>
<p><strong>MoCivil Aviation = Vision 2040’ Document - 1bn passenger traffic by 2040</strong></p>
<h3>Advantage for indian aviation&nbsp;</h3>
<p><strong>2011 - 2017 = nearly doubled passenger traffic.&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>LOW entry barrier market.+ untapped potential tourism</li>
<li>foreign to India travel&nbsp; = dominated by foreign travel companies. Indian co. can tap it.</li>
<li>Demand Robust = rising middle class + demography favourable&nbsp;</li>
<li>MRO opportunity&nbsp;</li>
<li>FDI in Civil Aviation =&nbsp; $2.5 bn in 2020-2021&nbsp;</li></ul>
<h3>Challenges&nbsp;</h3>
<ul>
<li>Financial Viability
<ul>
<li>ATF&nbsp;fuel prices (40% cost in airline, globally 20%)&nbsp;</li>
<li><strong>MRO costs</strong> one of the highest (aircraft service abroad)&nbsp; - <strong>100% FDI </strong>allowed&nbsp;</li>
<li>ATF outside GST, hence cascading impact is high.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Financing poor?&nbsp;</li></ul></li>
<li>Manpower
<ul>
<li>trained , skilled manpower -&gt; wages unsustainable levels</li>
<li><strong>100% </strong>FDI in training etc&nbsp;</li></ul></li>
<li>INFRA
<ul>
<li>gaps in airport capacity planning -&gt; other connecting infra like taxi service to airport</li>
<li><em><strong>100% FDI in&nbsp;</strong></em>green and brown field airport = unviable -&gt; need VGF</li>
<li>REGIONAL connectivity&nbsp;</li></ul></li>
<li>SAFETY = e.g. Kerala TableTop Runway accident&nbsp;</li></ul>
<h3>Way forward</h3>
<ul>
<li>Govt policy support&nbsp;
<ul>
<li><strong><span style="background-color:#f1c40f">UDAN RCS</span></strong> = 56 airport made (<u><em><strong>2 heliports + 2 water aerodomes)&nbsp;</strong></em></u>&nbsp;- connect to smaller states + NER&nbsp;</li>
<li>Nabh Nirman (airport capacity expand by 5x)</li>
<li>National Civil Aviation policy 2016 - passenger (4x by 2022)&nbsp; + cargo traffic (10 mn T by 2027)</li></ul></li>
<li>‘Cargo Policy’ needed&nbsp;</li>
<li>ATF under GST + MRO in India&nbsp;</li></ul>
